"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89493","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-27","<p><strong>Where legal fees are paid by an employer on behalf of a former employee and are taxable, I can confirm that H M Revenue and Customs ensures that income tax and national insurance contributions is paid.</strong></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-27T16:34:43.7073867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89493/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89493/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-08-29","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what HM Revenue and Customs' policy is on recovering tax on benefits in kind received by former employees of a corporation for whom legal fees have been met by that corporation.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","207352"
