"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89512","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-21","<p>I refer the hon.Members to the written statement made on 10 September, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 37WS, in which my rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government (Eric Pickles), indicated his intention to write to leaders of principal councils asking them to consider the implications of the Jay report for their own authority. In the event he wrote jointly with my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Education (Nicky Morgan) on 24 September with copies to Chairmen of all Health and Wellbeing Boards in England. A copy of this letter can be seen at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/358979/140924_-_Rotherham_letter_joint_final.pdf.</p><p> </p><p>My rt. hon. Friend the Home Secretary (Theresa May) has also written in similar terms to Chief Constables with copies to Police and Crime Commissioners.</p><p> </p><p>Copies of both letters are attached.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","207872","2014-10-21T16:36:24.3744319Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89512/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89512/answer","207398 McCabe.pdf","207398 McCabe.pdf","Letters from DCLG/DfE and Home Office","Letters from DCLG/DfE and Home Office","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89512/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Offences against Children: Rotherham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he plans to take to implement the recommendations made in the Independent Inquiry into child sexual exploitation in Rotherham from 1997 to 2013.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","207398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89513","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-05","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government has not purchased any televisions in 2013 and 2014. To place this in context, the Department in the last Parliament under the previous Administration spent £22,527 on four flat-screen televisions, equivalent to £5,632 per television (as outlined in the answers of 1 September 2009, Official Report, column 1832W and 16 December 2009, Official Report, column 1265W.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-09-05T13:50:39.9835411Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89513/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89513/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department spent on the purchase of televisions in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","207209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89514","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-05","<p>Planning applications are determined in accordance with the development plan unless material considerations indicate otherwise. An emerging neighbourhood plan may be a material consideration. The National Planning Policy Framework sets out the weight that may be given to emerging plans in decision taking. We have set out in planning guidance where circumstances may justify the refusal of planning permission on the grounds that an application would be premature in relation to the emerging Local or neighbourhood plan. Any weight a relevant policy could carry in determining a planning application remains with the decision maker.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-09-05T13:25:22.8408143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89514/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89514/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Neighbourhood Development Plans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department gives on the weight that should be given to a neighbourhood or village plan that has been submitted to a planning authority when considering planning applications.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bingham","High Peak","Andrew Bingham","207308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89515","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-05","<p>The Firefighters' Pension Scheme 2015 does not have a cap on the amount of pension that a firefighter can earn. This means that every year that the firefighter pays employee contributions into the 2015 scheme, they will earn more pension. This is the case whatever age the firefighter joined the 2015 scheme, including if they transferred across from the Firefighters' Pension Scheme 1992 after joining at age 18.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2014-09-05T13:32:12.823651Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89515/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89515/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will introduce transitional protection in the proposed 2015 pension scheme for those firefighters who joined the service and the pension scheme at age 18 years, and will have made a full contribution before the earliest age at which they could retire within the scheme.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","207279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89516","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-05","<p>Valuations of the Firefighters' Pension Schemes in England are undertaken in accordance with Directions issued by the Treasury under the Public Service Pensions Act 2013. The Directions ensure that valuations of the Firefighters' Pension Schemes are carried out every four years and that there is a transparent and consistent approach to valuations across public service pension schemes.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2014-09-05T13:34:06.5210092Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89516/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89516/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy that the firefighters' pension scheme be subject to a formal actuarial evaluation every three years.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","207278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89517","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-05","<p>Park home sites can be jointly owned by home owners and run on a co-operative model. We have not taken steps to promote this. Our priority has been to tackle poor management practices in the sector which is why we have implemented the Mobile Homes Act 2013, which significantly increases the rights of home owners and provides them with better protection.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-09-05T13:28:41.7975284Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89517/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89517/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Mobile Homes: Cooperatives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent steps he has taken to encourage the ownership and management of park homes on a cooperative model.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","207404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89518","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-09","<p>The Government announced that up to £2 million will be made available to Eastbourne Council to help them recover from the fire at Eastbourne Pier. HM Treasury will provide additional funding as required and this will be agreed as part of the 2014-15 Supplementary Estimates. The £2 million funding to Easbourne Council will be used to support local businesses and traders. None of the funding will be provided for the rebuilding of the pier itself, which, I understand is covered by the Pier owner's insurance.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2014-09-09T14:31:53.3532369Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89518/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89518/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89518/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","Piers: Eastbourne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, under what cost heading Eastbourne Pier has been granted money to help in its reconstruction.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Turner","Isle of Wight","Mr Andrew Turner","207426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89519","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Recast of the Energy Performance of Buildings Directive came into force on 19 May 2010, with a transposition date of 9 January 2013.</p><p>The Departmental portfolio includes EU Regulations that do not require transposition such as the EU Construction Products Regulation which was adopted in March 2011 and came fully into force in July 2013 and the European Structural and Investment Funds Regulations.<br><br>It is the Department's policy under this Government to avoid and reverse the gold-plating of EU directives by the Labour Government; for example, we have done this on the Energy Performance of Buildings Directive by scaling back the rules on Energy Performance Certificates to the minimum requirements of the directive and scrapping Home Information Packs.<br><br>We also wish to renegotiate powers back to the United Kingdom where appropriate; as a small but pertinent example, my Department has successfully removed the legal requirement in the European Regional Development Fund Regulations (introduced in 2006 under the Labour Government) to fly the EU flag outside our building for one week a year after Europe Day.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-10-13T15:18:10.2439827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89519/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89519/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-08-29","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many new EU directives and regulations have been transposed into UK law by his Department since May 2010.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","Mr John Redwood","207254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89520","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-08","<p>Since January 2010, DCMS has transposed four EU directives into UK law; and four EU regulations have come into effect within our areas of responsibility.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-08T13:14:22.099141Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89520/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89520/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-08-29","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many new EU directives and regulations have been transposed into UK law by his Department since May 2010.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","Mr John Redwood","207255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89521","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-08","<p>Ofcom’s October 2013 Infrastructure Report reported that download modem sync speeds in May 2013 were 17.7Mbit/s for the UK, 17.6Mbit/s for South East England, 19.2Mbit/s for Berkshire, and 18.5Mbit/s for the Royal Borough of Windsor and Maidenhead. Average upload speeds were not published in the infrastructure report. However in Ofcom’s UK fixed-line broadband performance report for November 2013 reported an average actual upload speed of 2.3Mbit/s for UK residential fixed-line broadband connections, but they did not publish a geographic breakdown.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-08T13:10:49.1688115Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89521/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89521/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-08-29","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the average (a) download and (b) upload speed in (i) the UK, (ii) the South East, (iii) Berkshire and (iv) Windsor constituency was on the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","207534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89522","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-08","<p>A list of the eligible applications to the Arts Council in the last three years in the sub-art form “Brass and Silver bands” will be placed in the libraries of both Houses. However, some activity for which brass bands play a constituent part may not be included, as the wider activity has not been classified specifically as such. Ineligible applications are not recorded by sub-art form.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-08T13:08:29.7046372Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89522/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89522/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-08-29","Brass Bands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many requests for funding have been made to the Arts Council by brass bands in each of the last three years; and how many such requests were (a) accepted in full, (b) accepted in part and (c) rejected.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","207353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89523","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-08","<p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport has not purchased any televisions in the periods stated.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-09-08T13:13:35.5859893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89523/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89523/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-08-29","Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department spent on the purchase of televisions in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","207210"
