"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89536","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-09-08","<p>We enjoy close cooperation with Saudi Arabia in countering the shared terrorist threat against both our countries. The Saudi Arabian government has condemned acts of terrorism and extremism around the world. In his Eid speech to mark the end of the holy month of Ramadan, King Abdullah was unequivocal in his language warning of the threat of extremism and sectarianism. The Saudi Arabian Government operates one of the most advanced de-radicalisation programmes anywhere and is working to reduce the threat that religious extremists pose including through the establishment of the King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz International Centre for Inter-religious and Intercultural Dialogue, opened in 2012 to enable, empower and encourage dialogue among followers of different religions and cultures around the world. We hope it will deliver practical initiatives to further that aim.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-09-08T14:20:03.7407107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89536/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89536/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-08-29","Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effect on the UK's security of the Saudi government's promotion of intolerant religious teachings internationally.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","207389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89537","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>The Army is not directly seeking to recreate ' Pals' regiments under Army 2020. Pals regiments were historic First World War formations mainly raised through the efforts of local authorities, industrialists or committees of private citizens and were composed of men who lived in a particular city or district, or who shared a common social or occupational background.<br>Army units, both Regular and Reserve, remain a key part of UK society and their local communities. Many continue to have a natural affinity to a particular part of the country in their recruiting. We encourage all serving Reservists to ‘bring a friend’ along to training. Significant work has gone into ensuring that there is an effective regional footprint of Army Reserve units under Army 2020. This, coupled with a strong recognition of the benefits of local and regional recruiting activity, alongside a wider national profile for the Army Reserve are key parts of the growth and investment in the Reserve Forces under Army 2020.<br><br>The Reserve Forces and Cadets Associations continue to play an important role in maintaining and developing that profile.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-09-04T12:52:07.5814219Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89537/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89537/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress he has made in establishing pals reservists regiments as part of Army 2020.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","207368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89538","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-05","<p>None. UAV Tactical Systems Ltd, a joint venture company owned by Elbit and Thales, is a sub-contractor of Thales UK, the prime contractor for the Watchkeeper programme. It is the responsibility of prime contractors to select and manage the performance of their sub-contractors.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-05T12:23:25.6062864Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89538/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89538/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of Elbit's performance in the Watchkeeper programme.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","207383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89539","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>As a member of the US coalition, the UK is committed to countering ISIL in Iraq and Syria. British personnel have been providing logistical, liaison and surveillance support in Iraq and will continue to do so. From 27 September 2014, following the parliamentary vote, the RAF began flying strike missions over Iraq. We have also recently sent a small team to provide short term training to Kurdish forces. These troops are not deployed in a ground combat role.<br><br>Additionally, as part of our preparations for a potential humanitarian airlift from the Sinjar Mountains in August, we deployed military personnel to Erbil. These troops were recovered to Cyprus when it became clear that the operation would not go ahead.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T16:20:56.8135416Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89539/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89539/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89539/answer/previousversion/18504","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any British military personnel have been deployed to (a) Northern Iraq, (b) Iraqi Kurdistan and (c) Northern Syria since June 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","207379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89540","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p>Copies of JSP 411, Defence Records Management Policy and Procedures, version 4.3 and 4.2 have been placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-04T14:57:53.4684443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89540/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89540/answer","jsp441_defence_records_mgt_policy_procedures_v4_2[1].pdf ; 20140402-JSP 441 Version 4.3-FINAL-U[1].pdf","jsp441_defence_records_mgt_policy_procedures_v4_2[1].pdf ; 20140402-JSP 441 Version 4.3-FINAL-U[1].pdf","JSP 441 Defence Records Management v4.2 ; JSP 411 Defence Records Management v4.3","JSP 441 Defence Records Management v4.2 ; JSP 411 Defence Records Management v4.3","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89540/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","Departmental Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of JSP 411-Defence Records Management Policy and Procedures, versions 4.3 and 4.2.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","207302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89541","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-11","<p> </p><p>Iraqi security force losses of military equipment since January 2014 cannot be accurately quantified. Known losses of equipment supplied by NATO members include howitzers and their tractors, an armoured personnel carrier and numerous vehicles, small arms and munitions. We continue to monitor the situation closely.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-11T15:15:56.0988814Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89541/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89541/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89541/answer/previousversion/18506","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","Defence Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the amount of military equipment supplied to Iraq by NATO states that has been appropriated by ISIS in 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","207376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89542","Home Office","false","2014-09-05","<p> </p><p>The majority of the Summit costs will be met by Her Majesty's Government. The overall final costs are expected to be reported formally after the Summit has concluded.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-09-05T13:20:45.7811579Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89542/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89542/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-08-29","NATO","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what his most recent estimate is of the cost of policing the NATO summit in Newport.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","207377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89543","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-05","<p> </p><p>Since commencement of the Ministry of Defence-TNT Pan Government Records Management Contract on 18 Dec 2003, no files have been lost by TNT archive services.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-05T12:22:02.2974595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89543/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89543/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-08-29","TNT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many files have been lost by TNT archive services in each year of the existing contract.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","207299"
