"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89579","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-09-04","<p>The Department recognises the potential for tidal energy in the UK and remains committed to explore the options of harnessing this resource.</p><p>Tidal energy developments are currently supported by Renewable Obligation Certificates (ROCs) until 2017. Thereafter they will be supported by Contract for Difference (CfD) under the Electricity Market Reform.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-09-04T15:41:57.7044107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89579/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89579/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89579/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-08-29","Tidal Power: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps are being taken by his Department to invest in tidal energy development in north-west England.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","207512"
