"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89596","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-09-05","<p> </p><p>The Government already makes available up-to-date advice to owners when travelling with their dogs in cars. The advice is available on the GOV.UK website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/animal-welfare-in-severe-weather" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/animal-welfare-in-severe-weather</a>.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-09-05T11:44:53.4234279Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89596/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89596/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-08-29","Dogs: Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will introduce new guidelines to protect the welfare of dogs in cars; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","207134"
