"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89625","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-09-05","<p>On 26 June, the former Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, the Rt Hon member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) welcomed the appointment of experts to the Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights Investigation on Sri Lanka. As his statement noted: ‘the inclusion of Martti Artisaahri, Silvia Cartwright and Asma Jahangir completes a strong team with a clear mandate from the UN Human Rights Council’ to investigate alleged violations and abuses on both sides of Sri Lanka’s military conflict. The UK played a key role in securing the investigation.</p><p>The full statement can be found at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/news/foreign-secretary-welcomes-announcement-of-un-investigation-team-on-sri-lanka</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-09-05T11:07:22.1912527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89625/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89625/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-08-29","Sri Lanka","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the merits of the appointment of a team of experts led by the UN Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights to assist the investigation into alleged abuses in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","207273"
