"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89648","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-09-05","<p>The Government takes seriously any reports that British components may have been used by Israeli forces during Operation Protective Edge. However, neither the Foreign and Commonwealth Office nor our Embassy in Tel Aviv have received any reports on the use of components for Paveway II bombs being used by the Israeli military forces during the recent fighting.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-09-05T14:18:31.3730372Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89648/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89648/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-08-29","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received of the use of components for Paveway II bombs manufactured by Raytheon in Scotland by Israeli military forces during Operation Protective Edge.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","207102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89649","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-09-03","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend, the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) issued a press release on 23 July stating that:</p><p>&quot;Today's UN Human Rights Council resolution will not help achieve a lasting ceasefire. It is fundamentally unbalanced and will complicate the process by introducing unnecessary new mechanisms.</p><p>The UK could not support this resolution, but recognising the strength of feeling about the loss of life and the desire by a large number of members of the Council to express that feeling in a resolution, the UK joined other EU nations in abstaining in the vote.&quot;</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-09-03T14:17:00.0518731Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89649/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89649/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-08-29","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, for what reason the UK abstained from voting on the motion entitled, Ensuring respect for international law in the Occupied Palestinian Territory, including East Jerusalem at the 21st Special Session of the UN Human Rights Council.","false","Biography information for Anas Sarwar","Glasgow Central","Anas Sarwar","207437"
